---
import StfLayout from '../../layouts/StfLayout.astro';
import StfBackNav from '../../components/StfBackNav.astro';
---

<StfLayout title="SPREAD THE FUNDS — Terms & Conditions">
  <StfBackNav />

    <main class="pt-24 pb-20 px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1
          class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold uppercase tracking-[4px] mb-2"
          style="color: var(--stf-text);"
        >
          TERMS & CONDITIONS
        </h1>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[2px] mb-10"
          style="color: var(--stf-text-dim);"
        >
          LAST UPDATED: MARCH 27, 2026
        </p>

        <div class="prose">
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using Spread the Funds ("the Service"), you agree to
            be bound by these Terms & Conditions. If you do not agree to these
            terms, please do not use the Service.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            Spread the Funds is a bill-splitting application that allows users
            to create groups, add shared expenses, adjust splits, and track
            settlements in real-time. The Service facilitates group expense
            coordination and tracking.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>
            You must be at least 18 years of age and capable of entering into a
            binding agreement to use the Service. By using the Service, you
            represent and warrant that you meet these requirements.
          </p>

          <h2>4. User Accounts</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your
              account credentials.
            </li>
            <li>
              You are responsible for all activities that occur under your
              account.
            </li>
            <li>
              You agree to provide accurate and complete information when
              creating your account.
            </li>
            <li>
              You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your
              account.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. User Conduct</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any
              applicable laws
            </li>
            <li>
              Misrepresent your identity or affiliation with any person or
              entity
            </li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure</li>
            <li>
              Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the Service to transmit harmful, offensive, or fraudulent
              content
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the Service for money laundering or other financial crimes
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>6. Funds and Contributions</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Fund creators are responsible for the accurate description and
              management of their funds.
            </li>
            <li>
              Contributions made through the Service are subject to processing
              by third-party payment providers.
            </li>
            <li>
              Refund policies for contributions are determined by the fund
              creator and applicable law.
            </li>
            <li>
              We are not responsible for disputes between fund participants.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>7. Fees and Payments</h2>
          <p>
            Certain features of the Service may require payment. All fees are
            described within the application. Payment processing is handled by
            third-party providers, and their terms also apply to transactions
            made through the Service.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The Service, including its design, features, and content, is owned
            by Spread the Funds and is protected by intellectual property laws.
            You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works of the
            Service without our written permission.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, Spread the Funds and its
            operators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
            consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the
            Service. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you have
            paid to use the Service in the 12 months preceding the claim.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without
            warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not warrant
            that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the
            Service at any time, with or without cause. You may terminate your
            account at any time by contacting us.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms & Conditions from time to time. Continued
            use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the
            updated terms.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the
            laws of the Province of Ontario, Canada, without regard to its
            conflict of law provisions.
          </p>

          <h2>14. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms & Conditions, please contact us at
            <a
              href="mailto:spreadthefund@gmail.com"
              style="color: var(--stf-primary);">spreadthefund@gmail.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
</StfLayout>
